properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 4 at 4:44AM PST until January 7 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with isolated gusts from 60
to 70 mph.

* WHERE...San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland
Empire, San Bernardino County Mountains, Riverside County
Mountains, Santa Ana Mountains and Foothills, San Diego County
Mountains and San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning.

* WHEN...From Sunday evening through Tuesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds and difficult driving conditions for
high profile vehicles on I-15, I-10 and I-8 through the
mountain passes. Other impacted areas include I-215 and Hwy
210 below the Cajon Pass.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The Santa Ana winds will be strongest at
the usual wind prone site like Fremont Canyon in the Santa Ana
Mountains, Sill Hill in the San Diego County Mountains, and
near San Bernardino and Fontana in the San Bernardino Mountain
foothills. Gusts from 60 to 70 mph are most likely in these
areas.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY EVENING THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING
